-- Russia May Approve $300 Million for Serbia’s Budget, Tanjug Says
-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 2012-09-04T11:16:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-04/russia-may-approve-300-million-for-serbia-s-budget-tanjug-says.html
Serbia  and  Russia  are close to
reaching an agreement on a $300 million loan for the Balkan
country to support its budget, the  Tanjug  newswire reported,
citing a Serbian government official.  Funds from the loan would become available by mid-December
and may be followed by another to support Serbia’s 2013 budget,
Tanjug quoted Natural Resources and Mining Milan Bacevic as
saying after he met in Moscow today with Russian Energy Minister
Alexander Novak.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  